pr_body:
This change suggested by @dean0x7d fixes ``SEVERE: Duplicate ID`` warnings and missing anchors in case of overloads. Here's an example that reproduces the problem (requires Sphinx version https://github.com/sphinx-doc/sphinx/commit/1021f4cdd71d2bb484b37c9b0acb87150c39aaa7)

```c++
/** Test */
char operator"" _format(const char *s, std::size_t);

wchar_t operator"" _format(const wchar_t *s, std::size_t);
```
but I guess the same may apply to other overloads.

Here are some more details: https://github.com/cppformat/cppformat/pull/207#issuecomment-149341656.

I'm not sure what's the best solution here. @michaeljones, do you think options should be passed to `renderer_factory_creator_constructor.create_factory_creator` at all?

This PR adds support for django-CMS-3.4 and djangocms-text-ckeditor-3.1 and higher.
When merged it will trigger a version jumpt to 0.12.0.

@pcolmant please review it, since it is going to superseed your PR #210.

I purposely did not add any other classes that have custom fields as I wanted to try it out for a bit.  

@levi-rs does this look like an acceptable approach to you?

I wish there were a way to return the correct type, for example if the value of a field is of a milestone id to return the milestone instance but afaik there is no way of knowing.

Add new example: based character-level cnn for chinese text classification.
 I've implemented the [Highway Networks](https://arxiv.org/pdf/1505.00387.pdf) architecture.The final train model is CNN + Highway Network structure, and this version can achieve a best dev accuracy of 94.75% with the Chinese corpus.
